        "text": "Acts 21:18",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " (see notes). The manifestation to James—only mentioned here—the chief of our Lord’s formerly unbelieving brothers (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "John 7:5",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), explains the presence of “His brothers” amongst the 120 disciples at Jerus. (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 1:14",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") and James’ subsequent leadership in the mother Church. His high position at the time of writing accounts for his citation in this place. Paul made acquaintance with James as well as Peter on his first visit to the Jerus. Church (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Galatians 1:18",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " f.). The well-known story about the meeting of Jesus with James told by Jerome (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "De viris illustr",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "., 2) implies an earlier date for this than Paul’s narrative admits of, since ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ἔπειτα",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " signifies succession in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "time",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; succession of ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "rank",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " cannot be intended.—“After that, to all the apostles”: in this formal enumeration, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ἀπόστολοις",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " bears its strictest sense, and could hardly include James (see ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 1:13",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " f.; he is not certainly so styled in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Galatians 1:19",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). Paul was, presumably, aware of the absence of Thomas on the occasion of ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Corinthians 15:5",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", and his consequent scepticism (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "John 20:24",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " ff.); he therefore says distinctly that ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "all",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " participated in this latter sight, which coincides in point of time with ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 1:6-12",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", not ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "John 20:26",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The witness of the First App. to the resurrection was complete and unqualified.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
